<major-heading id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2008-06-30.0.mh" nospeaker="True" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-08/wa0630.htm">Written Answers Monday 30 June 2008</major-heading>

<major-heading id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2008-06-30.1.mh" nospeaker="True" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-08/wa0630.htm">Scottish Executive</major-heading>

<minor-heading id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2008-06-30.S3W-14271.h" nospeaker="True" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-08/wa0630.htm#1">Maternity Services</minor-heading>

<ques id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2008-06-30.S3W-14271.q0" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/80310" speakername="Ross Finnie (West of Scotland) (LD)" spid="S3W-14271" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-08/wa0630.htm#1">

  <p>To ask the Scottish Executive what guidance it issues on the number of nurses per child designated to care for (a) sick and (b) premature babies in intensive care.</p>

</ques>


<reply id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2008-06-30.S3W-14271.r0" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/80396" speakername="Nicola Sturgeon" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-08/wa0630.htm#1">

  <p>Care should be responsive to the needs of babies and their parents, and organised so that the most appropriate and experienced professional is the care provider at any given time, in accordance with the needs of the baby. Regarding neonatal care for sick and premature babies, the Scottish Government recommend that NHS boards adopt the neonatal levels of care model set out in table 21 of <em>A Framework for Maternity Services in Scotland (2001)</em> , when considering the provision of immediate and neonatal care. This model is based on the British Association of Perinatal Medicine guidelines.</p>

</reply>


<minor-heading id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2008-06-30.S3W-14466.h" nospeaker="True" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-08/wa0630.htm#2">Police</minor-heading>

<ques id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2008-06-30.S3W-14466.q0" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/80308" speakername="Patricia Ferguson (Glasgow Maryhill) (Lab)" spid="S3W-14466" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-08/wa0630.htm#2">

  <p>To ask the Scottish Executive whether the additional police officers funded through Glasgow&rsquo;s Community Planning Partnership are in addition to the Scottish Government&rsquo;s target complement.</p>

</ques>


<reply id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2008-06-30.S3W-14466.r0" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/80341" speakername="Kenny MacAskill" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-08/wa0630.htm#2">

  <p>Yes, the additional police officers funded through Glasgow&rsquo;s Community Planning Partnership are in addition to Strathclyde&rsquo;s share of the 1,000 additional recruits that the government is funding.</p>

</reply>


<minor-heading id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2008-06-30.S3W-13938.h" nospeaker="True" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-08/wa0630.htm#3">Rail Network</minor-heading>

<ques id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2008-06-30.S3W-13938.q0" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/80321" speakername="Christine Grahame (South of Scotland) (SNP)" spid="S3W-13938" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-08/wa0630.htm#3" holdingdate="2008-06-19">

  <p>To ask the Scottish Executive what provision for financing the Waverley line was in place prior to 18 May 2007.</p>

</ques>


<reply id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2008-06-30.S3W-13938.r0" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/80393" speakername="Stewart Stevenson" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-08/wa0630.htm#3">

